==Description==

The '''TechDraw ExtensionPosObliqueChainDimension''' tool aligns oblique dimensions to create a chain dimension.

[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionPosObliqueChainDimensionExample.png|400px]]
{{Caption|On the right the aligned dimensions}}

==Usage==

# Select two or more parallel oblique dimensions.
# The first dimension defines the position. This dimension will not be moved.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionPosObliqueChainDimension.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_ExtensionPosObliqueChainDimension|Position Oblique Chain Dimensions]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Extensions: Attributes/Modifications → [[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionPosHorizChainDimension.svg|16px]] Position Oblique Chain Dimensions}} option from the menu.
# The dimensions are aligned.


